Janet's ducks lay 16 eggs per day. She eats 3 eggs for breakfast and uses 4 eggs to bake muffins. The total number of eggs used in the day is:

$$
3 \text{ (breakfast)} + 4 \text{ (muffins)} = 7 \text{ eggs}
$$

Subtracting this from the total eggs laid:

$$
16 \text{ eggs} - 7 \text{ eggs} = 9 \text{ eggs}
$$

She sells the remaining 9 eggs at $2 per egg:

$$
9 \text{ eggs} \times \$2/\text{egg} = \$18
$$

**Final Answer:**
#### 18
